{"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MM4CenterType"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For non-carbon atoms, the center type reflects what it would be, if the atom"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"were replaced with a carbon, and its lone pairs replaced with hydrogens.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Methane carbons are disallowed in the simulator, as they will be simulated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"very inaccurately. The fluorine parameters struggle with the edge case of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"carbon tetrafluoride, and HMR creates the nonphysical carbon-8 isotope. In","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"general, primary sp3 carbons are also discouraged, for the same reasons"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that methane is prohibited."}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4centertype"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"topicSections":[{"title":"Enumeration Cases","identifiers":["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4CenterType\/primary","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4CenterType\/quaternary","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4CenterType\/secondary","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4CenterType\/tertiary"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4CenterType\/init(rawValue:)"],"title":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4CenterType\/Equatable-Implementations","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4CenterType\/RawRepresentable-Implementations"]}],"hiera